--------------------------------------------------
GENERAL PRINCIPLES
--------------------------------------------------

- Always use TypeScript with strict typing.
- Never use `any`.
- Prefer explicit types and interfaces.
- Keep components small and reusable.
- Separate UI, business logic, and data access.
- Follow clean architecture principles.
- No duplicated logic.
- Use async/await properly with error handling.
- Always handle edge cases.

--------------------------------------------------
PROJECT STRUCTURE
--------------------------------------------------

Use this folder structure:

/app
  /(marketing)
  /(dashboard)
  /api
/components
  /ui
  /dashboard
  /interview
/lib
  /ai
  /db
  /utils
  /types
/hooks
/services

--------------------------------------------------
ARCHITECTURE RULES
--------------------------------------------------

- All business logic goes inside /services.
- All AI-related logic goes inside /lib/ai.
- All DB access goes inside /lib/db.
- Components must never directly call external APIs.
- Use Server Actions for mutations.
- Prefer Server Components when possible.
- Use Client Components only when needed.

--------------------------------------------------
UI RULES
--------------------------------------------------

- Use TailwindCSS only (no inline styles).
- Follow clean SaaS design (minimal, modern).
- Use consistent spacing scale.
- Use semantic HTML.
- Ensure accessibility (aria labels when needed).
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders.

--------------------------------------------------
STATE MANAGEMENT
--------------------------------------------------

- Prefer server state.
- Use React hooks only when necessary.
- Avoid global state unless justified.
- Keep forms controlled and typed.

--------------------------------------------------
INTERVIEW LIVE MODE (IMPORTANT)
--------------------------------------------------

When generating interview simulation features:

- Structure code to support:
  - Audio input
  - Video input
  - Streaming responses
  - Persona-based interviewer behavior
- Keep interview logic separate from UI.
- Design extensible persona system:
  - strict
  - aggressive
  - calm
  - technical
- Prepare architecture for real-time AI streaming.

--------------------------------------------------
CODE QUALITY
--------------------------------------------------

- Write readable code.
- No console.log in production.
- Add meaningful comments only when necessary.
- Use clear naming conventions.
- Use functional components only.
- Use async error boundaries when needed.

--------------------------------------------------
PERFORMANCE
--------------------------------------------------

- Optimize for performance.
- Avoid unnecessary client components.
- Lazy load heavy features.
- Use dynamic imports when needed.

--------------------------------------------------
SCALABILITY
--------------------------------------------------

- Design as if 100k users will use it.
- Avoid tight coupling.
- Keep AI layer swappable.
- Keep database abstraction clean.

--------------------------------------------------
OUTPUT EXPECTATION
--------------------------------------------------

When generating code:
- Always output complete files.
- Include types.
- Include proper imports.
- Follow project structure.
- Do not generate placeholder logic.
- Write production-ready code.